Lateral line almost complete; pored tubes visible from pterotic-supracleithrum to caudal peduncle; one plate, usually sixth or seventh, without lateral line tube, but canal may continue in skin. Abdomen with numerous small dermal platelets, without naked area. Pectoral girdle entirely exposed ventrally; coracoids entirely covered with odontodes; 
arrector fossae
round, small, not meeting at midline, covered by skin (
Fig. 2
). Odontodes evenly distributed, regularly arranged on head and body. Enlarged odontodes on anterior and lateral margin of snout, bordering upper lip.
